Three people died and two were injured when a bakkie overturned on the N2 in the direction of Esikhawini, Empangeni, near Richards Bay on Sunday afternoon. Netcare 911 paramedics worked alongside other services on the scene, Netcare 911 spokeswoman Athlenda Mathe said. When paramedics arrived on the scene, they found that three men had been ejected out of the bakkie and had already succumbed to their injuries. They were all declared dead at the scene. A woman and another man sustained moderate to minor injuries. They were stabilised on the scene and thereafter transported to a nearby hospital for further medical care. The cause of the accident was not yet known. African News Agency (ANA)